t_city   = \n| country_largest_city_population    = \n| country_leader_title               = \n| country_leader_name                = \n| country_area_sqmi                  = <!-- or |country_area_sqft= or |country_area_acre= -->\n| country1                          = \n| country1_admin_divisions_title    = \n| country1_admin_divisions          = \n| country1_admin_divisions_title_1  = \n| country1_admin_divisions_1        = \n| country1_capital_type             = \n| country1_capital                  = \n| country1_largest_city_type        = \n| country1_largest_city             = \n| country1_capital_and_largest_city = \n| country1_largest_city_population  = \n| country1_leader_title             = \n| country1_leader_name              = \n| country1_area_sqmi                = <!-- or |country1_area_sqft= or |country1_area_acre= -->\n| demonym          = \n| population       = \n| population_as_of = \n| population_footnotes = \n| population_rank =\n| population_rank_max =\n| density_sqmi     = \n| density_rank     =\n| density_footnotes = \n| ethnic_groups    = \n| timezone1        = [[Atlantic Standard Time|AST]]\n| utc_offset1      = -4\n| timezone1_DST    = \n| utc_offset1_DST  = \n| website          = \n| additional_info  = private island<br>{{Infobox protected area\n| name = Balliceaux Island Cultural Landmark\n| alt_name = \n| iucn_category = III\n| photo = \n| photo_caption = \n| map = \n| relief = 1\n| map_caption = \n| location = \n| nearest_city = \n| coordinates = \n| coords_ref = \n| area_acre = \n| area_km2 =142.07 \n| area_ref = \n| authorized = \n| established = proposed\n| visitation_num = \n| visitation_year = \n| visitation_ref = \n| governing_body = \n| website = [https://www.protectedplanet.net/balliceaux-island-cultural-landmark Balliceaux Island in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]\n}}\n| footnotes       = \n}}\n\n'''Baliceaux''' is a small, privately owned <ref name=\"sale\" /> [[Caribbean]] island and is one of the [[Grenadines]] chain of islands which lie between the larger islands of [[Saint Vincent (island)|Saint Vincent]] and [[Grenada]]. Politically, it is part of the nation of [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]].<ref name=\"sea\">{{in lang|fr}} [https://www.sea-seek.com/sites.php?lien=Baliceaux-Island-St-Vincent- Baliceaux Island (St Vincent)]</ref>\n\n== History ==\nDiscovered by Spanish navigators during the fifteenth century, this island of 1,35 km\u00b2 enjoyed a long and interesting history. It got prominence during wars 1769 - 1795 within the Caribbean region. Island highest point ''Gun Hill'', almost 126 meters above sea level, served as an observation station for soldiers between 1772\u20131797.\nIn the 1790s, the British army banished about 5000 [[Black Caribs]] to Baliceaux following the defeat of the rebellion of Carib Chief [[Joseph Chatoyer]] in [[Saint Vincent (Antilles)|Saint Vincent]]. Their descendants live today as the [[Garifuna people]] in [[Honduras]], [[Belize]], [[Guatemala]], [[Nicaragua]] and in the [[United States]].\n\nThe island had a small area where the Black Caribs that died from disease were buried. This has since been eroded over time by wind and sea, and very little remains of the area where the people were buried.<ref name=\"sea\" />\n\nTo commemorate these events every year in March ''Pilgrimage to Balliceaux'' is held. It coincides with ''National Hero's Day'' in St. Vincent. <ref>[https://www.uncommoncaribbean.com/grenadines/tracing-the-roots-of-garifuna-settlement-day-back-to-balliceaux-in-the-grenadines/ Tracing the Roots of Garifuna Settlement Day Back to Balliceaux in the Grenadines]</ref>\nThe cultural landmark status is proposed for Baliceaux island.<ref>[https://www.protectedplanet.net/balliceaux-island-cultural-landmark Balliceaux Island in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[First Carib War]]\n*[[Second Carib War]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Commons Category|Baliceaux}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Islands of Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]\n[[Category:Private islands]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]\n\n{{SaintVincent-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox islands\n| name             = Baliceaux\n| native_name      = Balliceaux\n| native_name_link = \n| native_name_lang =\n| sobriquet        = <!-- or |nickname= -->\n| image_name       = Baliceaux2.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| image_caption    = Baliceaux Island\n| image_alt        = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_size         = \n| map_caption      = \n| pushpin_map             = Saint Vincent and the Grenadines#Lesser Antilles#Caribbean\n| pushpin_label           = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_relief          = 1\n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates      = {{coord|12|57|00|N|61|08|45|W|display=inline,title|region:VC_type:isle_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n| etymology        = \n| location         = [[Caribbean]]\n| grid_reference   = <!-- UK only -->\n| archipelago      = [[Grenadines]] \n| waterbody        = \n| total_islands    = \n| major_islands    = \n| area_acre        = 320\n| area_footnotes   = <ref name=\"sale\">[https://www.nytimes.com/real-estate/vct/vc/other-saint-vincent-and-the-grenadines/homes-for-sale/balliceaux-island/2836-YQWYLB Balliceaux Island] [[New York Times]]</ref>\n| rank             = \n| length_mi        = <!-- or |length_ft= -->\n| length_footnotes = \n| width_mi         = <!-- or |width_ft= -->\n| width_footnotes  = \n| coastline_mi     = <!-- or |coastline_ft= -->\n| coastline_footnotes = \n| elevation_ft     = \n| elevation_footnotes = \n| highest_mount    = 126 m. Gun Hill\n| country          = {{VCT}}\n| country_admin_divisions_title      = \n| country_admin_divisions            = \n| country_admin_divisions_title_1    = \n| country_admin_divisions_1          = \n| country_admin_divisions_title_2    = \n| country_admin_divisions_2          = \n| country_capital_type               = \n| country_capital                    = \n| coun