'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|'''[[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk|Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]]'''\n|2018\u201319\n|15||1||1||0||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||16||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|'''[[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]'''\n|2019\u201320\n|19||1||2||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2013||24||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|'''Career total'''\n!'''324'''||'''8'''||'''30'''||'''0'''||'''20'''||'''2'''||'''2'''||'''0'''||'''376'''||'''10'''\n|}\n\n===Notes===\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Honours==\n;Litex Lovech\n* [[Bulgarian A Football Group|A Group]]: [[2009\u201310 A Group|2009\u201310]], [[2010\u201311 A Group|2010\u201311]]\n* [[Bulgarian Cup]]: [[2008\u201309 Bulgarian Cup|2008\u201309]]\n* [[Bulgarian Supercup]]: [[2010 Bulgarian Supercup|2010]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|pid=17902}}\n\n{{PFC CSKA Sofia squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zanev, Petar}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:PFC Litex Lovech players]]\n[[Category:RC Celta de Vigo players]]\n[[Category:Racing de Ferrol footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Volyn Lutsk players]]\n[[Category:FC Amkar Perm players]]\n[[Category:FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk players]]\n[[Category:PFC CSKA Sofia players]]\n[[Category:Bulgaria international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian expatriates in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Russia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Petar Zanev\n| image               = Petar Zanev 2017.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| caption             = Zanev in 2017\n| fullname            = Petar Dimitrov Zanev\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1985|10|18}}\n| birth_place         = [[Blagoevgrad]], Bulgaria\n| height              = {{height|m=1.83}}<ref>{{cite web|publisher=7sport.net|url=http://www.7sport.net/archive7ds/2011/09/01/fb_nacionali/d6206_12.htm|title=\u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d \u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u043f\u043e-\u0432\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a\u0438|date=1 September 2011|accessdate=29 April 2015|language=Bulgarian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208124138/http://www.7sport.net/archive7ds/2011/09/01/fb_nacionali/d6206_12.htm|archivedate=8 December 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| position            = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Left back]]\n| currentclub         = [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]\n| clubnumber          = 11\n| youthyears1         = \n| youthclubs1         = \n| years1              = 2003\u20132005 | clubs1 = [[FC Pirin Blagoevgrad|Pirin Blagoevgrad]]  | caps1 =  15 | goals1 = 1\n| years2              = 2005\u20132012 | clubs2 = [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]]           | caps2 = 124 | goals2 = 4\n| years3              = 2007\u20132008 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Celta de Vigo|Celta]] (loan)            | caps3 =   3 | goals3 = 0\n| years4              = 2008      | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Racing de Ferrol|Racing Ferrol]] (loan) | caps4 =  14 | goals4 = 0\n| years5              = 2012\u20132013 | clubs5 = [[FC Volyn Lutsk|Volyn Lutsk]]              | caps5 =  22 | goals5 = 0\n| years6              = 2013\u20132018 | clubs6 = [[FC Amkar Perm|Amkar Perm]]                | caps6 = 115 | goals6 = 2\n| years7              = 2018\u20132019 | clubs7 = [[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk|Yenisey]]          | caps7 =  15 | goals7 = 1\n| years8              = 2019\u2013     | clubs8 = [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]               | caps8 =  19 | goals8 = 1\n| totalcaps           = \n| totalgoals          = \n| nationalyears1      = 2006\u2013\n| nationalteam1       = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 43\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 07:05, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 26 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Petar Dimitrov Zanev''' ({{lang-bg|\u041f\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0414\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432}}; born 18 October 1985) is a [[Bulgaria]]n professional [[association football|footballer]]. He plays for the [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgarian national team]] and [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]] and is usually deployed as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]] for both club and country. For the club side he more frequently plays [[centre-back]] in the last year.\n\n==Club career==\nZanev was born in [[Blagoevgrad]] and joined the [[youth system]] of his hometown club [[OFC Pirin Blagoevgrad|Pirin]] at an early age. In early 2005 he signed with [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]].\n\n===Celta (loan)===\nOn 17 June 2007, [[Celta de Vigo|Celta]] manager [[Hristo Stoichkov]] unveiled Zanev as the club's first signing ahead of 2007\u201308 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20070620/sport/stoichkov-to-stay-in-charge-of-celta.13899|publisher=timesofmalta.com|title=Stoichkov to stay in charge of Celta|accessdate=20 June 2007}}</ref> On the next day, Zanev signed for the Spanish [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]] side on a season-long loan deal, with the club having the option to make the move permanent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://football.sportal.bg/news.php?news=52250|publisher=[[sportal.bg]]|title=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043e\u0442\u0441\u0442\u044a\u043f\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u043b\u0442\u0430|accessdate=18 June 2007|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> On 26 August, he made his league debut in their 1\u20131 draw against [[C\u00f3rdoba CF]], but spent most of his time with Celta on the bench, making only three appearances. Because of this, midway through the season his contract was terminated.\n\n===Racing Ferrol (loan)===\nOn 9 January 2008, [[Racing de Ferrol|Racing Ferrol]] confirmed Zanev has joined on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vsekiden.com/20341|publisher=vsekiden.com|title=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432 \u043e\u0442\u0438\u0434\u0435 \u0432 \u0420\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u0424\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043b|accessdate=9 January 2008|language=Bulgarian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110105134057/http://www.vsekiden.com/20341|archivedate=5 January 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He made his debut on 27 January in a 3\u20131 away win over [[SD Eibar]], coming on as a substitute for [[Jonathan Pereira Rodr\u00edguez|Jonathan Pereira]]. Zanev appeared 14 times for Ferrol in the [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\n===Return to Litex===\nZanev returned to [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]] at the end of the 2007\u201308 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.segabg.com/online/article.asp?issueid=3003&sectionid=12&id=0002101|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120918012646/http://www.segabg.com/online/article.asp?issueid=3003&sectionid=12&id=0002101|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 September 2012|publisher=segabg.com|title=\"\u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441\" \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u0441 \u0442\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0438 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432|accessdate=17 June 2008|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> On 18 May 2011, he scored his second league goal in his career in a 4\u20131 win over [[PFC Montana|Montana]]. Zanev's third official goal for Litex came on 19 July 2011, netting the first of a 3\u20130 home win over [[FK Mogren|Mogren Budva]] in the second qualifying round of the Champions League, this also being Zanev's first European goal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000260/match=2007503/postmatch/report/index.html|publisher=uefa.com|title=Litex Lovech 3\u20130 Mogren (agg: 5\u20131)|accessdate=19 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Volyn Lutsk===\nIn early July 2012, Zanev signed a three-year contract with [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] club [[FC Volyn Lutsk|Volyn Lutsk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sport.bnt.bg/index.php/futbol/bg-futbol/zanev-podpisa-s-volin-luck|publisher=sport.bnt.bg|title=\u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0441 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d (\u041b\u0443\u0446\u043a)|accessdate=28 August 2012}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n===Amkar Perm===\nZanev signed with [[Russian Football Premier League|Russian Premier League]] side [[FC Amkar Perm|Amkar Perm]] on 30 June 2013 on a three-year deal. He was given the number 3 jersey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.novsport.com/news648231_1004.html|publisher=novsport.com|title=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432 \u0435 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0442\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u043d \u0432 \u0410\u043c\u043a\u0430\u0440 (\u041f\u0435\u0440\u043c)|date=30 June 2013|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n===Yenisey Krasnoyarsk===\nOn 25 June 2018, following the bankruptcy of Amkar, he joined [[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]] that was promoted for the first time into the [[Russian Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]]|url=https://xn----jtbalgbx7av.xn--p1ai/2018/06/26/%D0%BF%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%80-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B5%D0%B2-%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BB-%D0%B8%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BC-%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%B5%D1%8F/|title=\u041f\u0415\u0422\u0410\u0420 \u0417\u0410\u041d\u0415\u0412 \u0421\u0422\u0410\u041b \u0418\u0413\u0420\u041e\u041a\u041e\u041c \"\u0415\u041d\u0418\u0421\u0415\u042f\"|date=25 June 2018|language=Russian}}</ref> He left Yenisey on 3 April 2019.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Yenisey Krasnoyarsk]]|url=https://xn----jtbalgbx7av.xn--p1ai/2019/04/03/%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B5%D0%B2-%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%BD%D1%83%D0%BB-%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%B5%D0%B9/|title=\u0417\u0410\u041d\u0415\u0412 \u041f\u041e\u041a\u0418\u041d\u0423\u041b \"\u0415\u041d\u0418\u0421\u0415\u0419\"|date=3 April 2019|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\n===CSKA Sofia===\nOn 29 May 2019 CSKA Sofia announced to have signed a contract with Zanev, following a period when he was training with the team.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://cska.bg/index.php?main_page=document_general_info&products_id=8108 | title = \u041e\u043f\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0417\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0432 \u0449\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0435\u0437\u043e\u043d | language = Bulgarian | author=|publisher = CSKA Sofia | date= 29 May 2019|accessdate = 29 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nIn 2006 [[Hristo Stoichkov]] called up the left back to the [[Bulgaria national football team]]. Zanev made his official debut for [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] in a friendly match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] on 15 November 2006. The result of the match was a 1:3 loss for Bulgaria. He was [[sent off]] (after receiving a second caution) for the first time on 15 October 2013, in the 0:1 home loss against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] in a World Cup qualifier.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=topsport.bg|title=Bulgaria vs. Czech Republic Matchcast|url=http://topsport.ibox.bg/football.live.php?match=77082|date=15 October 2013|accessdate=28 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150227012344/http://topsport.ibox.bg/football.live.php?match=77082|archive-date=27 February 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> After being overlooked for the Euro 2016 qualifiers, Zanev's good performances in the [[Russian Premier League]] saw him make a return to the national side for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 World Cup qualification matches]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bulgaria NT vs. Belarus NT 1:0|url=http://www.flashscore.com/match/SpwiXi02/#lineups;1|publisher=flashscore.com|date=13 November 2016|accessdate=19 November 2016|language=English}}</ref> On 7 October 2017, he [[captain (association football)|captained]] the national team, in the 0:1 home loss against [[France national football team|France]] in a 2018 World Cup qualifier.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=687977| title = \u0413\u043e\u043b \u043e\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043b\u043d\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u044a\u0440\u0448\u0438 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \"\u043f\u0435\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0435\" (\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043e+\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0440\u0438\u044f)| language = Bulgarian | author=|publisher = sportal.bg| date= 7 October 2017|accessdate = 8 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n[[File:Petar Zanev.JPG|thumb|Zanev playing for [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]] in 2009]]\n{{Updated|3 March 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|'''[[FC Pirin Blagoevgrad|Pirin Blagoevgrad]]'''\n|2003\u201304\n|5||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||5||0\n|-\n|2004\u201305\n|7||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2013||colspan=2|\u2013||8||0\n|-\n!'''Total'''\n!'''12'''||'''0'''||'''1'''||'''0'''||'''0'''||'''0'''||'''0'''||'''0'''||'''13'''||'''0'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|'''[[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]]''